WASHINGTON (AP) — D.C. United goalkeeper Bill Hamid will be sidelined for two-to-three months following surgery on his left hand.The team said Friday that Hamid had the operation on June 30 with Dr. Peter Thomas of OrthoVirginia to repair a ruptured ligament.The 31-year-old played for D.C. from 2009-17, joined Denmark’s Midtjylland in 2018, then rejoined D.C. that August. Hamid has made eight appearances for the United States.___More AP soccer: https://apnews.com/hub/soccer and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports